<h2>When Is It Time to Redesign Your Business Website?</h2>
<p>Your website is often the first impression a customer gets of your business. If that impression is slow, outdated, or confusing, you're losing customers before you even know they visited. For most Kenyan businesses, a website redesign is overdue every <strong>3–5 years</strong>, but there are clear signs you shouldn't wait that long.</p>

<h2>7 Signs You Need a Website Redesign</h2>
<ol>
  <li><strong>It looks bad on mobile</strong>, If your site isn't fully responsive, you're alienating 80%+ of your visitors.</li>
  <li><strong>It loads slowly</strong>, If your site takes more than 3 seconds to load, most users will leave before seeing it.</li>
  <li><strong>You can't update it yourself</strong>, A website you depend on your developer to update is a liability.</li>
  <li><strong>It doesn't reflect your current brand</strong>, New services, new branding, new team, your site should match.</li>
  <li><strong>You're not getting enquiries from it</strong>, Your website should be generating leads. If it isn't, something is wrong.</li>
  <li><strong>It's not ranking on Google</strong>, Old sites often lack the technical SEO signals Google looks for in 2024.</li>
  <li><strong>Your competitors' sites look better</strong>, Credibility is relative. If your competitor's site looks more professional, customers will choose them.</li>
</ol>

